cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a new class of neural networks based on systems theory and recurrent neural networks (RNNs). Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates the proposed models on three different tasks, indicating a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely sub-categories. The use of systems theory and the focus on high-level layers suggest cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the experiments involve image classification, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as a possible sub-category.
